  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 20th level, if you die you can choose to become an incorporeal entity on the border-ethereal plane at the spot you died in the material plane at the start of your next turn. This entity has the physical ability scores (Strength, Dexterity, Constitution) and abilities of a ghost, but has your mental ability scores (Intelligence, Wisdom, Charisma) and your psion class abilities.</p>\n<p>When you take this, your current and maximum hit points becomes that of the ghost. While you are in the form, if you have less than 10 psi points when you would assume this form, you now have 10 psi points. While in this form you cannot rest to regain spent abilities. If you exhaust all Psi Points or the ghost is destroyed, you die as a normal creature would.</p>",
